There are four transport modes in [[Main/en/OpenTTD|OpenTTD]]: Rail, Road, Sea and Air. Each has its own construction method.


*[[File:en/Railroad build button.png]] '''[[Main/en/Railway construction]]''' - Build [[Main/en/Railway station|train stations]], connecting [[Main/en/Building tracks|railway track]], and [[Main/en/signals]] for [[Main/en/trains]].
*[[File:en/Road build button.png]] '''[[Main/en/Roadway construction]]''' - Build either [[Main/en/Loading Bays#Bus Loading Bay|bus stations]] and [[Main/en/Loading Bays#Lorry Loading Bay|truck stations]], and connect them with roads for [[Main/en/buses]] and [[Main/en/Road vehicles|trucks]].
*[[File:en/Dock build button.png]] '''[[Main/en/Waterway construction]]''' - Build [[Main/en/docks]], [[Main/en/waypoints|buoys]], [[Main/en/canals]] for [[Main/en/ships]] to follow.
*[[File:en/Airport build button.png]] '''[[Main/en/Airport construction]]''' - Build [[Main/en/airports]] and direct [[Main/en/Aircraft|planes]] between them.

